    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once the onion is starting to soften, add your<strong> lean beef mince </strong>to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 4 min further, or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
